<code class="lh-copy">
  There are several places you can store your .vimrc file, so the $MYVIMRC variable is mapped to the
  currently loaded .vimrc file which is also equivalent to the first .vimrc file found.
  You can open the file by typing :e $MYVIMRC
</code>
